# Leadsbot Development Rules

## Project Context
- Building an AI-powered real estate lead follow-up agent
- React + TypeScript + Vite + AWS Amplify Gen2
- Custom CSS modules (NO Tailwind)
- Premium theme styling (Cuba, Porto, Metronic quality)

## Styling Requirements
- Use CSS Modules for all styling
- Create premium admin theme with sophisticated design
- Color palette: Deep blues (#1e3a8a, #3b82f6), elegant grays (#1f2937, #374151)
- Typography: Inter font family, clear hierarchy
- Spacing: 8px-based system (8, 16, 24, 32, 48, 64px)
- Components: Cards, buttons, forms, tables with subtle shadows and modern styling

## Architecture Guidelines
- Component-based structure with reusable UI components
- CSS Modules naming: `ComponentName.module.css`
- Global styles in `src/styles/global.css`
- Design tokens in `src/styles/tokens.css`
- Responsive design with mobile-first approach

## Code Quality
- TypeScript strict mode
- ESLint compliance
- Semantic HTML and accessibility
- Performance optimization
- Clean, maintainable code structure

## Dependencies
- Only use existing packages in package.json
- No additional third-party libraries without approval
- Leverage AWS Amplify UI components when possible

## File Structure
```
src/
├── components/
│   ├── ui/           # Reusable UI components
│   ├── layout/       # Layout components
│   └── forms/        # Form components
├── styles/
│   ├── global.css    # Global styles
│   ├── tokens.css    # Design tokens
│   └── components/   # Component-specific styles
├── pages/            # Page components
├── hooks/            # Custom React hooks
├── utils/            # Utility functions
└── types/            # TypeScript type definitions
```

## Premium Theme Standards
- Professional admin dashboard aesthetic
- Clean, modern interface design
- Consistent spacing and typography
- Subtle animations and micro-interactions
- Dark/light theme support
- Mobile-responsive design 